verbose_text: Transgenic neonatal mice expressing extra copy of extracellular superoxide dismutase (EC-SOD) had a significant reduction in ROS and improved angiogenesis in neonatal mice lung following exposure to hyperoxia, while EC-SOD knocked out mice had reduced neovascularization, increased endothelial dysfunction and worsening lung injury when compared to controls [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: EC-SOD knocked out mice had reduced neovascularization, increased endothelial dysfunction and worsening lung injury
